{"cursor":"21506","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Complex adaptive systems' are special cases of complex systems, often defined\nas a 'complex macroscopic collection' of relatively 'similar and partially\nconnected micro-structures' â formed in order to adapt to the changing\nenvironment, and increase its survivability as a macro-structure.\n\nThey are 'complex'; in that they are dynamic networks of interactions, and their\nrelationships are not aggregations of the individual static entities. They are\n'adaptive'; in that the individual and collective behavior mutate and self-\norganize corresponding to the change-initiating micro-event or collection of\nevents. ","linknr":463,"url":"Complex_adaptive_system","recorded":1362476898,"links":41,"instances":["statistics","sociology","biology"],"pdf":["http://psych.lse.ac.uk/complexity/Papers/Ch2final.pdf","http://psych.lse.ac.uk/complexity/Papers/Ch2final.pdf","http://web.eecs.utk.edu/~mclennan/papers/EPCSST.pdf","http://web.eecs.utk.edu/~mclennan/papers/EPCSST.pdf","http://www.dodccrp.org/files/IC2J_v4n2_03_Phister.pdf","http://www.dodccrp.org/files/IC2J_v4n2_03_Phister.pdf","http://web.mit.edu/esd.83/www/notebook/Complex%20Adaptive%20Systems.pdf","http://web.mit.edu/esd.83/www/notebook/Complex%20Adaptive%20Systems.pdf","http://www.uow.edu.au/~kd21/uploads/Diment-complexity.pdf","http://www.uow.edu.au/~kd21/uploads/Diment-complexity.pdf"],"categories":["Complex systems theory","Systems","Business theory","Organizational theory|","Social psychology","Social sciences","Sociocultural evolution"],"headings":["Overview","Modeling and Simulation","Evolution of complexity","See also","References","Literature","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Complex-adaptive-system.jpg/250px-Complex-adaptive-system.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.2